    },
    {
      "suggestedId": "emilkowalski-interruptibility-rapidly-triggered-or-gesture-driven",
      "source": "emilkowalski",
      "text": "Interruptibility. Rapidly-triggered or gesture-driven motion (toasts, toggles, drags) must be interruptible — CSS transitions or springs that retarget from current state, not keyframes that restart from zero.",
